Title: Nonlinear Constraints from Non-Abelian Internal Symmetries
Authors: Ludwik Turko
Comments: 4 pages, to appear in Nuclear Physics Proceedings Supplement:
  STATISTICAL QCD, held at Bielefeld August 2001
Report-no: December 2001 IFT UWr 01/12/2001
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. A702 (2002) 361-365
\\
  Symmetry invariant local interaction of a many body system leads to global
constraints. We obtain explicit forms of the global macroscopic condition
assuring that at the microscopic level the evolution respects the overall
symmetry.
